Such synonyms as the following (sometimes with a slightly different shade of meaning) have a distinctly Ciceronian ring about them, and have in fact been exactly paralleled by Weinkauff and others: animi et ingenii, clamore plausuque, dzottzae et opes, sama et laus, vtis et facultas, memoria et recordatio, modestia ac pudore, operae curaeque.
